India allows the use of fifteen different types of identification, ranging from property documents to arms licenses to income tax identity cards. Included, too, are forms of identification most likely to be possessed by the poor.
Sweden‚Äôs policy is a bit more vague, requiring that a voter who is not known to the voting clerks [produce] an identity document or in another way verify her or his identity.

Canada permits any voter who lacks one of the allowed forms of photo identification to present two of forty-five other forms of identification or documentation. Acceptable documents include leases, student transcripts, and utility bills.

‚ÄúIn Switzerland, every registered voter is sent a registration card prior to an election, and if the voter brings her registration card to the polling place, no additional identification is needed.‚Äù
